'''''Granny's Garden''''' is an educational [[adventure game]] for the British [[BBC Micro]] computer, released in 1983.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Only the Best BBC Micro Games / BBC Games from the past - Classic Games |url=https://www.bbcmicrogames.com/bestrest.html |access-date=2022-07-13 |website=www.bbcmicrogames.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pixelatron.com/blog/grannys-garden-creator-interview/ |title=Granny's Garden creator interview |access-date=2022-07-13 |language=en-US}}</ref> It served as a first introduction to computers for many schoolchildren in the United Kingdom during the 1980s and 1990s. According to the 4Mation webpage about the original version, it was the reason many teachers decided that computers had a real place in education.<ref name="mation1">{{cite web|url=http://www.4mation.co.uk/retro/retrogranny.html |title=Retro Granny's Garden |publisher=4mation.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-02-19}}</ref> The software is still available in its original<ref name="mation1"/> and updated<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.4mation.co.uk/cat/granny.html |title=Granny's Garden |publisher=4mation.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-02-19}}</ref>  formats.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-09-06 |title=From Weird Dreams to Granny's Garden: a brief history of cursed video games |url=http://www.theguardian.com/games/2019/sep/06/weird-cursed-video-games-spectrum-commodore-playstation |access-date=2022-07-13 |website=the Guardian |language=en}}</ref>

Created by Mike Matson for 4Mation, the game takes place in the Kingdom of the Mountains. The aim is to find the six missing children of the King and Queen, while avoiding the [[Witchcraft|evil witch]], by solving puzzles.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Cobbett|first=Richard|date=2019-11-16|title=Crapshoot: The nightmare realm of Granny's Garden|language=en|work=PC Gamer|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/crap-shoot-grannys-garden/|access-date=2022-01-09}}</ref>

